The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety and efficacy of the gene-activated bone substitute consisting of octacalcium phosphate and plasmid DNA encoding vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) for maxillofacial bone regeneration.

 The patients with congenital and acquired maxillofacial bone defects and alveolar ridge atrophy will be enrolled.

